{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a4a94cc6-67ad-4cd2-87e0-76ef24fa020a","content":"The directory doesn't exist yet, but I can tell you exactly what you need to configure to publish a C# MCP server as a `dotnet tool`.\n\n### Required `.csproj` properties\n\nAdd these to your `MyMcpServer.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <!-- Makes it a dotnet tool -->\n  <PackAsTool>true</PackAsTool>\n  <ToolCommandName>my-mcp-server</ToolCommandName>\n\n  <!-- Required for NuGet publishing -->\n  <PackageId>MyMcpServer</PackageId>\n  <Version>1.0.0</Version>\n  <Authors>YourName</Authors>\n  <Description>An MCP server for ...</Description>\n  <PackageProjectUrl>https://github.com/you/repo</PackageProjectUrl>\n  <PackageLicenseExpression>MIT</PackageLicenseExpression>\n\n  <!-- Console app is required for stdio transport -->\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n### Key points\n\n- **`PackAsTool`** is the critical property — it packages the app as a globally/locally installable dotnet tool.\n- **`ToolCommandName`** sets the CLI command name users will run.\n- **`OutputType`** must be `Exe` for stdio-based MCP servers.\n\n### Publish steps\n\n```bash\n# Pack\ndotnet pack -c Release\n\n# Push to NuGet.org (get API key from nuget.org/account/apikeys)\ndotnet nuget push bin/Release/MyMcpServer.1.0.0.nupkg \\\n  --api-key YOUR_API_KEY \\\n  --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n### Users install with\n\n```bash\ndotnet tool install --global MyMcpServer\nmy-mcp-server   # runs via stdio\n```\n\nWould you like me to create or update your `.csproj` file with these settings?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3ec0594a-6f14-455d-b58f-c2ca70ad256f","outputTokens":483,"requestId":"5036:B3321:D43094:F4C082:69F2AC38"},"id":"008e8055-9774-4728-9cce-a88884a6e454","timestamp":"2026-04-30T01:11:28.748Z","parentId":"9cd72a0b-1806-4c11-894d-3d88f3a79fe3"}
